
1. Install LM-Sensors

These sensors are a requirement in order to have Conky installed properly.

    A. From the terminal, enter the following: sudo apt-get install lm-sensors
    B. Configure the sensors by entering the following: sudo sensors-detect
    C. Reply "yes" to all of the questions.
    D. Test what is being detected by entering "sensors." This will display all detected sensor devices.

2. Installing and Running Conky

    A. From the terminal, enter the following: sudo apt-get install conky
    B.  Copy file ( .conky ) in folder Panacea-Bar to you're home directory. 
    C. To start Conky. Press <ALT> + <F2> and enter ( conky ).
